4. Area of natural forests, riverine areas and wetlands under formal community protection

Outcome 1
1. Number of certified organic farmers/farms
2. Increased density and diversity of native tree species in cyclone damaged landscapes around Apia covering  3314 ha
3. Area of natural forests, riverine areas and wetlands under protection and management in the production landscape under community  landuse plans (forest and tree cover maintenance; maintenance of wetlands; no net increase of agricultural land under mono cropping)
4. Number of farmer households adopting at least one or more soil / water management and conservation practices on agricultural lands
5. Increased water quality as a consequence of enhanced watershed management and water source protection
6. Per cent of Livestock relocated to optimal grazing areas away from critical riparian areas
