     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Objective:
1. Increased vegetation cover in at least 10% of total area covered by the project = &gt; 25,000 ha.
2. 76,000 + Y ha of added forest area under KBA Management Plans to be developed under the project. Y to be determined at end of project
3. At least 500 Households benefitting - men and women equally from adopting SAPs and/or conservation practices.
4. Avoided emission of 689333 CO2-eq for 4 years and sequestration of store additionally 10,755 tCO2eq.

Outcome1:
1. A 30% increase in number of households engaged in organic farming or adopt ecosystems-based farming practices
2. At least 50% of landscape around Apia total area shows increase in forest cover, and 10% increase diversity.
3. By the end of the project, at least 55000 ha will be under integrated landscape management outside KBAs
4. At least 500 households will be adopting soil management and conservation practices in their land by the end of the project covering at least 1,800 ha
5. Water quality monitoring guidelines for livestock management areas approved by Water Resources Division and demonstrated at 3 sites
6. 50% (2500ha) riparian areas cleared of livestock.
7. t least ten (10) villages with Integrated SLM Plans, with at least one key priority implemented.
8. At least 750 community members have demonstrated SLM principles through agricultural practices on their farms and within their KBA boundaries.

Outcome 2:
9. Farmer Field Manuals on Soil management and soil conservation developed, with case studies on SLM practices for agriculture, such as agro-forestry, agro-ecosystems approach to agriculture, and water resources management.
10. &#x2022;	Land resources management legislation developed and national policy updated; 
&#x2022;	Agriculture Sector Plan 2011 - 2016 strengthened to mainstream SLM approaches and management practices
&#x2022;	Update to reflect the Agriculture Sector Plan 2016-2020.
&#x2022;	Policies on mining (including sand mining) strengthened or developed
&#x2022;	Formal Guidelines for SLM under village development plans under PUMA Act developed
11. Score 5
12. SLM mainstreamed in Sector-wide Coordination mechanism under the Samoa Development Strategy and NESP
13. Number of NGOs and private partners in SLM is increased by 200%. 
14. A SLM information system in place, linked with the data knowledge information facility (DKIF) and building on the national land administration system.
15. At least 100 staff from MNRE, MAF, MWCSD have completed a professional level SLM training
16. Revised Diploma in Sustainable Agriculture at NUS with specific emphasis on SLM.</narrative>
